	{
		"slug": "chat-sse-tool-call",
		"description": "Server-sent events tool-call happy path for POST /agents/{a}/conversations/{c}/messages/stream. The multi-turn `chatScript` drives the dispatcher's tool-call loop deterministically: turn 1 emits a `list_kbs` tool call (a built-in tool that needs no external dependency and returns a fixed string on an empty workspace), turn 2 emits the final answer. Pins the full intermediate-iteration SSE shape: `user-message` -> `token-reset` -> `tool-call` -> `tool-result` -> `token`* -> terminal `done`. The closing GET confirms the user-facing transcript is just the user turn + final assistant row (the tool-call/tool-result scaffolding rows are persisted but filtered from the message list).",
		"chatScript": {
			"turns": [
				{
					"toolCalls": [
						{
							"id": "call-list-kbs-1",
							"name": "list_kbs",
							"arguments": "{}"
						}
					],
					"tokenCount": 4
				},
				{
					"tokens": ["You have ", "no knowledge bases ", "yet."],
					"tokenCount": 7
				}
			]
		},
		"steps": [
			{
				"method": "POST",
				"path": "/api/v1/workspaces",
				"body": { "name": "w", "kind": "mock" }
			},
			{
				"method": "POST",
				"path": "/api/v1/workspaces/$1.workspaceId/agents",
				"body": { "name": "fixture-tool-agent" }
			},
